-- Al-Mal of Kuwait Rises to Highest in More Than A Year on Stake Sale Offer
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2010-11-03T08:05:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/al-mal-of-kuwait-rises-to-highest-in-more-than-a-year-on-stake-sale-offer.html
Al-Mal Investment Co.  surged to the
highest level in more than a year after the Kuwaiti firm said it
received an offer to sell a 31.3 million-dinar ($112 million)
stake in an energy company.  The shares increased 4.4 percent to 144 fils, the highest
intraday level since September 2009, as of 10:37 a.m. in Kuwait.
The shares have gained 73.5 percent this year.  Al-Mal said it will decide on a possible sale this month
and it may make a 20.5 million-dinar gain from the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
